# Evidence-First Turn Proof

This artifact captures the mission outcome for the default evidence-first,
observable REPL turn model.

## Prior Failure Mode

Before this slice, repository questions could stay on a hidden synthesizer-side
retrieval path and return weak generic prose without visible routing steps or
default file citations.

Representative symptom:

```text
>> How does memory work in paddles?
[INFO] Context assembly (initial) produced 5 hit(s), retained 5 artifact(s), pruned 0.
Chord Response: To help you understand how memory works in PaddleS, I could suggest that we have a look at the documentation...
```

That behavior hid the retrieval path and did not ground the answer in cited
repository evidence.

## New Default Repository-Question Route

Live command:

```bash
just paddles --prompt "How does memory work in paddles?"
```

Observed turn stream:

```text
• Classified turn
  └ repository-question
• Routed turn
  └ repository question will use gatherer lane 'sift-autonomous' (SiftAutonomous) before synthesizer lane 'qwen-1.5b'
• Checked gatherer capability
  └ sift-autonomous: available
• Gathered context with sift-autonomous
  └ Autonomous `heuristic` gatherer collected 5 evidence item(s) for `agent_memory agents.md implementation memory paddles reload source` across 1 turn(s); stop reason: no-further-queries.
    Sources: src/infrastructure/adapters/agent_memory.rs, README.md, ARCHITECTURE.md, POLICY.md
• Reviewed planner trace
  └ strategy=heuristic, turns=1, steps=1, stop=no-further-queries
```

Grounded cited synthesis is also covered by regression tests:

- `application::tests::repository_questions_use_gatherer_lane_when_available`
- `infrastructure::adapters::sift_agent::tests::repository_turns_fall_back_to_grounded_evidence_when_model_is_confused`

Those tests prove that repository questions take the explicit gatherer path and
that weak model synthesis degrades to cited evidence instead of unsupported
repository prose.

## Gatherer-Missing Fallback

Live command:

```bash
just paddles --gatherer-provider context1 --prompt "How does memory work in paddles?"
```

Observed turn stream:

```text
• Classified turn
  └ repository-question
• Routed turn
  └ repository question will use gatherer lane 'context-1' (Context1) before synthesizer lane 'qwen-1.5b'
• Checked gatherer capability
  └ context-1: harness-required: Context-1 requires a dedicated search harness. Re-run with --context1-harness-ready only when that external harness is actually available.
• Fell back
  └ gatherer: gatherer unavailable for a repository question: Context-1 requires a dedicated search harness. Re-run with --context1-harness-ready only when that external harness is actually available.
• Fell back
  └ grounded-synthesis: no explicit evidence bundle was available for this repository question
• Reported insufficient evidence
  └ No cited repository sources were available.
Chord Response: I couldn't gather enough repository evidence to answer `How does memory work in paddles?` confidently.

Sources: none
```

This proves the controller no longer pretends that gatherer-backed evidence ran
when the gatherer is unavailable.

## Default Action Stream For Workspace Actions

Live command:

```bash
just paddles --prompt "What's the current git status"
```

Observed turn stream:

```text
• Classified turn
  └ deterministic-action
• Routed turn
  └ turn will stay on synthesizer lane 'qwen-1.5b' while gatherer lane 'sift-autonomous' (SiftAutonomous) remains available
• Ran shell command
  └ git status
• Completed shell
  └ Shell command: git status
• Synthesized direct answer
  └ No repository citations required for this turn.
```

This proves the Codex-style action stream is the default REPL UX rather than a
verbose-only mode.

